summary: Spider-Man: Far From Home Heads to Venice in Tom Holland's New Photo
title: Spider-Man: Far From Home Heads to Venice in Tom Holland's New Photo
excerpt: Tom Holland is reunited with two very familiar faces as Spider-Man: Far From Home filming moves to Venice.
description:
Principal photography on Spider-Man: Far From Home has shifted to Venice, Italy as Tom Holland joins to two familiar faces in a photo in the city’s iconic canals.

Holland posted a photo on his Instagram account with Ned Batalon and Zendaya as the production moves to its Italian location. It is the third European city to be filmed for the upcoming MCU sequel after principal photography began in London in July before moving to Prague.

RELATED: Spider-Man: Far From Home Photo Teases a Familiar Costume Upgrade

Next year’s Spider-Man sequel is expected to follow the events of Avengers 4 with a resurrected Peter Parker going on a summer vacation with his friends only to run into new villains overseas.

While Zendaya’s Michelle had previously been seen on set in Europe, Batalon’s prominent appearance in Holland’s post confirms Peter Parker’s high school friend Ned Leeds will also be joining his classmates on their European vacation.

RELATED: Spider-Man: Far From Home Set Photos Reveal Peter & Michelle in Prague

Helmed by returning director Jon Watts, Spider-Man: Far From Home stars Tom Holland, Zendaya, Jacob Batalon, Jake Gyllenhaal, Samuel L. Jackson, Cobie Smulders, Remy Hii, and Tony Revolori. It is scheduled to be released on July 5, 2019.

blog.name: donotgowherethepathmaylead
blog.title: Do Not Go Where The Path May Lead
blog.description: Welcome to my Fanblog. I'm your host and I am here to introduce you to as many of my fandoms as possible. so buckle up, this could take all day. Or several, as I have gone (and will continue to go) through a lot of phases – because let’s be frank, I love a lot, but I love a lot rather quickly. Some of My Past and Present Favs include: SG1, Quantum Leap, Miss Fisher’s Murder Mysteries, Cabin Pressure, Critical Role, Lucifer (Fox/Netflix), Good Omens (Book & Amazon Show), Doctor Who, Dramaworld, Star Wars, Fringe, Star Trek, Almost Human, The 10th Kingdom, Wynonna Earp, Supernatural, Sherlock, X-Files, Person of Interest, The Golden Girls, Melissa and Joey, Frasier, Castle, Firefly, Law & Order: CI, Merlin, SGA, ATLA, LoK, Lord of the Rings, Harry Potter and Marvel Films. I also have an eclectic taste for music and quotes. I'm fascinated by comics and video games, though I am by no means an expert in either (I do love Bioware's ME and DA series, Naughty Dog's Uncharted Series, Insomniac’s Spider-Man, CD Red Projekt's The Witcher Series and Telltale's The Wolf Among Us, to name a few). I also read a bunch of stories in varying forms, from novellas to comics and graphic novels. I essentially love all of the genres in both the visual, written and auditory mediums. I love immersing myself in new things, which I suspect is why I go through so many phases. If any of this interests you, than this is the blog for you to follow. If none of the previous tickles your fancy, stick around for a bit. You might get hooked on something new. If you're looking for something a little more serious, still fun mind you, but a little more focused and a little less Fandom fluid, than please check out My Main Blog. Fair Warning: Both blogs have a bit of overlap, so you'll occassionally see serious, Non-Fandom related, posts here, and you'll see Fandom related posts over there. :-)

summary: I realize I’m about to date myself by typing this, but I haven’t played a Spider-Man game since Spider-Man 2 on the Original...
body:
I realize I’m about to date myself by typing this, but I haven’t played a Spider-Man game since Spider-Man 2 on the Original XBox.

Playing Spider-Man on PS4 brought back such wonderful memories of playing 2. Not only that but it superseded my nostalgia — which I honestly didn’t think would be possible.

This is a wonderful game. The art style, story, music, gameplay, and faithfulness to the source materials — All beautifully came together to make this one of the best games I’ve played.

If you have not played it and you like the MCU, or any of the Comics or Cartoon adaptations, you need to play this game.

Oh, and heads up fellow webheads, this is a Marvel game. That means we stick around for the end credits. Twice.
